d butterfly whisk."},{"content":" <strong>Re-insert butterfly whisk<\/strong>. Place cream into mixing bowl and whip <b>until soft peaks form\/speed 3<b>, watching carefully through hole in mixing bowl lid to avoid over whipping."},{"content":"Spread whipped cream mixture evenly over cooled roulade, leaving a 1 cm border around the edge. Space mandarin segments evenly on top of cream. Using long edge of the roulade, carefully roll into a tight log shape using the baking paper to assist in rolling. Remove paper. Place roulade seam side down onto a serving platter. Clean and dry mixing bowl."},{"content":"Place chocolate into mixing bowl and melt <b>2 min\/50°C\/speed 3<b>. Drizzle roulade with melted chocolate. Place into refrigerator to chill for approx. 30 minutes. Remove from refrigerator 15 minutes before slicing and serving. "}],"hintsAndTricks":["You can replace tinned mandarin segments with drained tinned fruit of choice or fresh strawberries."],"basicInfo":["medium","20m","1h 30m","6 portions"]}